## 📝 Quick Reference

### Aggregate Functions

| Function | What It Does | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `COUNT(*)` | Count all rows | `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM orders` |
| `COUNT(col)` | Count non-null values | `SELECT COUNT(phone) FROM customers` |
| `SUM(col)` | Add up values | `SELECT SUM(quantity) FROM orders` |
| `AVG(col)` | Calculate average | `SELECT AVG(price) FROM products` |
| `MAX(col)` | Highest value | `SELECT MAX(price) FROM products` |
| `MIN(col)` | Lowest value | `SELECT MIN(price) FROM products` |

### GROUP BY Syntax

```sql
SELECT   column, AGGREGATE(col)
FROM     table
WHERE    condition          -- filter rows first
GROUP BY column             -- then group
ORDER BY AGGREGATE(col) DESC;
```

### HAVING Syntax

```sql
SELECT   column, COUNT(*) AS total
FROM     table
GROUP BY column
HAVING   COUNT(*) > 5      -- filter groups after
ORDER BY total DESC;

### WHERE vs HAVING

| | WHERE | HAVING |
|---|---|---|
| Filters | Individual rows | Groups |
| Runs | Before GROUP BY | After GROUP BY |
| Works with | Any column | Aggregate functions |
| Example | `WHERE price > 1000` | `HAVING COUNT(*) > 5` |

---

### SQL Execution Order

```
1. FROM      → identify the table
2. WHERE     → filter rows
3. GROUP BY  → group filtered rows
4. HAVING    → filter groups
5. SELECT    → return columns
6. ORDER BY  → sort final result
7. LIMIT     → restrict row count
```

## ⚠️ Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---|---|
| Using WHERE to filter aggregates | Use HAVING instead |
| Selecting a column not in GROUP BY | Add it to GROUP BY or wrap in aggregate |
| Forgetting ROUND on AVG | `ROUND(AVG(price), 2)` |
| Using HAVING without GROUP BY | HAVING needs GROUP BY to work |

